parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to jerk, stutter, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This issue can also cause sudden loss of power, potentially leading to death or serious injury, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Abnormal noise from the rear of the vehicle
grinding or clunking noise from the drivetrain
and failure to move from a stationary position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DPF can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate, and hesitate, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving in traffic or on highways.
symptoms: the check engine light and glow plug lamp come on simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the fuel gauge can lead to inaccurate fuel level readings, causing drivers to run out of fuel, which can result in engine damage, accidents, or stranding.
The failure of the suspension can affect the vehicle's stability and handling, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or on rough roads.
symptoms: The suspension needs to be replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to latch properly can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt unlatches even when properly secured
the seat belt fails to latch into the receiver
the seat belt does not stay securely fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Absence of Automatic Locking Retractor (ALR) in Rear Center Seat
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of the ALR feature in the rear center seat can make it difficult or impossible to properly install a child's car seat, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear center seat lacks the ALR feature
making it incompatible with certain child car seats
the owner's manual incorrectly indicates the presence of ALR in all rear seating positions.
